{
  "texts": [
    "Task B: Word Puzzle involves word-type brain teasers, where the answer defies the default meaning of the word and focuses on the letter composition of the question.",
    "The training dataset comprises 132 multiple-choice QAs, each accompanied by its semantic and context reconstructions, resulting in a total of 396 multiple-choice QAs (3 × 132).",
    "These brain teaser categories include puns, homophones, ambiguous words, and various other linguistic puzzles, as showcased in the examples provided in Table2",
    "on the right-hand side.",
    "The Word Puzzle sub-task pose challenges not only for systems but also for humans in discerning the correct answer."
  ]
}